	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-24055">
		<div id="comment-24055">
		<div class="comment-gravatar"><img alt='' src='//0.gravatar.com/avatar/02fcbd9db7012534f8061e0a51364087?s=65&#038;d=mm&#038;r=x' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/02fcbd9db7012534f8061e0a51364087?s=130&amp;d=mm&amp;r=x 2x' class='avatar avatar-65 photo' height='65' width='65' /></div>

		<div class="comment-body">
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
		<cite class="fn">Kevin</cite><br/>
		<a href="http://www.sowrey.org/2007/11/bank-of-montreal-i-hate-your-security/#comment-24055">
			20 January 2014 at 13:59</a>		</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

		<p>BMO is still doing this even now.. I got a call from them telling me they locked my card again. This has happened 3 times in the last 12 months and they replaced the cards each time. I&#8217;m now looking for a new bank and credit card.</p>

		
		<div class="reply">
